ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It is a great introduction to physiology, which is the big picture material that students in the biomedical sciences don't always understand, but which is important for making their work medically relevant.
I would definitely recommend this class to other people.
In my opinion, ENAS 550 is a very useful course, especially for students with engineering backgrounds lacking biology knowledge.
I would recommend this course for another students if they were looking for a "big picture" view of physiology.

I would recommend it to people that have bio background; this class is very helpful, but if you can't put in a big chunk of your time, you might end up failing this class and other classes you're taking as well

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I am a biomedical Ph.D. student who usually works on small systems, so learning about physiology has been very important as I begin my graduate work, since it allows me to understand the larger systems in which I am working. I'm certain that, whatever physiological system I end up working in, this course will have informed my research in that field.
This course solidified material that I already learned.
It helps me a lot in doing biomedical engineering research
